Overview [#overview]
********************
*@{project.name} is a support library that aids Alien-Factory in the development of other libraries, frameworks and applications.
Though you are welcome to use it, you may find features are missing and the documentation incomplete.*

A valiant effort to parse HTML5 documents into XML.

'HtmlParser' currently recognises and supports:

Elements:
 - Normal elements: '<div></div>'
 - Void elements: '<br>'
 - Self closing elements: '<foreignElement />'
 - Raw text elements: '<script> ... </script>'
 - Escapable raw text elements: '<textarea> ... </textarea>'

Attributes:
 - Empty attributes: '<input disabled>'
 - Unquoted attributes: '<input type=submit>'
 - Single quoted attributes: '<input type='submit'>'
 - Double quoted attributes: '<input type="submit">'

Other:
 - Comments: '<!-- comment -->'
 - CData Sections: '<![CDATA[ cdata ]]>'
 - Numerical character references: '&#160;' and '&#xA0;'

doctype

Created so HTML documents created with [Slim]`pod:afSlim` may be parsed and tested by [Bounce]`pod:afBounce`.


While this should work with the majority of HTML documents, it's main focus is on parsing valid HTML5 documents. 
So while it may be lenient and allow self closing tags anywhere in the document (and not just in foreign elements),
you'll find things like character references and CDATA sections are not recognised in script and style elements.

Note that this is a parser and *NOT* a HTML5 validator so is considerably more lenient 

It also does *NOT* attempt to reconstruct documents from the tag soup of badly formatted HTML4 documents.

If your HTML is pretty good - 

the main things it strives to overcome is Void tags and valueless attributes.


